original_title: Kung Alam Ko Lang Na Walang Katapusan Ang Katapusan
overview: Distant childhoods are examined between two families: a Filipino family residing in the Philippines, and a Fil-Am family residing in the United States, through a series of vacation trip stills taken five years apart from each other.
tagline: It was unfortunate that happiness became genuine
title: If I Only Knew The End Never Ends
